article.headline: Western Kentucky 72, Arkansas State 70
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Courtney Lee scored a game-high 22 points as Western Kentucky slipped past Arkansas State 72-70 in the Sun Belt Conference opener for both teams Thursday. Sixteen of Lee's points came in the second half. Benson Callier scored 17 points and Ty Rogers added 11 for Western Kentucky (9-4, 1-0). ASU (5-10, 0-1) led by as many as 14, with 13:21 left in the second half, and never trailed in the game until Rogers connected on a pair of free throws with 3:51 left. Lorenzo Hampton hit a layup for two of his 12 points. Up one with 11 seconds left, the Hilltoppers' Anthony Winchester was fouled by Marcus Ardison. Winchester missed the front end and connected on the second to make the score 70-68. The Indians drove the length of the floor where Jim Jones found Ardison for a layup to tie the score at 70. Ardison turned and fouled Callier. Callier hit the first and missed the second with six seconds left. ASU got a brief chance when Kitus Witherspoon got the rebound but then lost the ball. A foul of Lee by Dereke Tipler with two seconds remaining sealed the win for Western Kentucky. Lee hit one of two free throw attempts. Lee and Winchester entered the game as the two top scorers in the league at 19.6 points per game. Winchester was held to 7 points and four rebounds.
